Illegal immigrants made hundreds of complaints last year about a private security company that runs removal centres.

G4S, which came under the spotlight last year when Angolan detainee Jimmy Mubenga died after being restrained on a flight, received 773 complaints in 2010.

The most common concerned lost property or poor communication - but others related to assault and racism.

